  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Dirac-like fermions and node-loop features in bilayer BC 3 sheet sandwiching a triangular alkaline metal layer</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2016-01-28</subfield>
    <subfield code="t">published</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="300" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">5</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Using density-functional calculations we have investigated the features of massless relativistic Dirac-like fermion and node-loop in bilayer BC 3 sheet sandwiching a triangular alkaline metal layer. Superposition of single-sheet spectra combined with the alkaline metal doping gives rise to the Dirac-like spectrum and an interesting node-loop on the Fermi surface, which is similar to that in AA-stacked bilayer graphene. Furthermore, the sandwich structures are thermodynamically and kinetically stable due to the presence of strong ionic bonding between alkaline metal layer and BC 3 sheets. The newly predicted structures can be taken as good candidates to investigate Dirac-like particles and 2D Dirac semimetal features.</subfield>
